President Joe Biden has authorized an increase in federal funding for disaster assistance in the state of New Mexico. This includes debris removal and emergency protective measures in response to wildfires and straight-line winds that occurred starting on April 5, 2022. The federal share for these expenses has been increased to 100% of the eligible costs for a 90-day period from the date of declaration. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.